  "extraction_notes": "REFLECTION 2 — FINAL RECONCILIATION. SERVES ADDITIONS: Added Microsoft company-level SERVES IT professionals — the filing explicitly names IT professionals as a target across server products spanning multiple segments, independently grounding this at company level. Added Outlook.com SERVES consumers and OneDrive SERVES consumers — both are consumer-facing offerings explicitly described in the M365 Consumer subsection. Added Nuance Healthcare SERVES large enterprises — the filing describes Nuance solutions deployed across healthcare systems which are large enterprise customers; however, healthcare organizations is already captured and is more specific, so not adding large enterprises to avoid weak inference. Added Surface SERVES large enterprises — the filing mentions 'organizations' as Surface customers; large enterprises is the closest canonical label but is a stretch from 'organizations.' Keeping as conservative inference since devices are sold to enterprises via commercial channels. SERVES REMOVALS: Removed Surface SERVES large enterprises on further reflection — 'organizations' is too vague to map to a specific canonical label; consumers is explicitly grounded and retained. MONETIZES_VIA ADDITIONS: Added Nuance Healthcare MONETIZES_VIA subscription — the filing groups Nuance cloud solutions under server products and cloud services revenue which is subscription-based. Added Microsoft Copilot MONETIZES_VIA advertising — Microsoft Copilot is described alongside Bing and Edge in the search and news advertising context. Added Outlook.com MONETIZES_VIA advertising — the filing describes Outlook.com alongside other consumer services monetized through advertising. Added OneDrive MONETIZES_VIA subscription — OneDrive storage is part of M365 Consumer subscription. Added Xbox Cloud Gaming MONETIZES_VIA subscription — explicitly part of Xbox Game Pass subscription. Added Power BI MONETIZES_VIA subscription — described as a cloud-based analytics service within M365 Commercial subscription context. SELLS_THROUGH ADDITIONS: Added Surface SELLS_THROUGH online — the filing mentions Microsoft Store as a sales channel for first-party devices. Added Microsoft 365 Consumer SELLS_THROUGH online — sold through Microsoft Store and app stores. SCOPE FIXES: Reviewed all company-level SELLS_THROUGH — all eight channels are independently grounded in the Distribution section and valid at company level. Reviewed all OPERATES_IN — five places all valid normalized geography. PARTNERS_WITH: Confirmed no explicit named partnerships in the filing; no PARTNERS_WITH triples needed. OFFERING AUDIT: Re-verified all 44 offerings against filing text. No missing named offerings found. Microsoft Partner Network confirmed as a named offering (partner services program). Azure AI Foundry confirmed as explicitly named. All offerings verified. DUPLICATE CHECK: Confirmed no unsupported company-level OFFERS duplicates — all offerings are anchored to segments. No company-level OFFERS triples present, which is correct since every offering has a segment anchor. LABEL CHECK: All canonical labels verified against allowed lists. IT professionals added to company-level SERVES.",
